#Approach:

Longest Subarray with Sum K – Sliding Window Approach

Jab array me sirf positive numbers aur 0 hote hain, tab sliding window use kar sakte hain
kyunki sum predictable way me behave karta hai.

Hum do pointers lete hain: left aur right.
Ye dono milkar current window ya subarray represent karte hain.
Saath me current window ka sum maintain karte hain.

Right pointer ko aage badhate jao aur current element ko sum me add karo.
Agar sum k se bada ho jaye, to left pointer ko aage badhao aur left wale elements ko sum se minus karo
jab tak sum k se chhota ya equal na ho jaye.

Jab bhi sum exactly k ke equal ho, current window ki length nikaal kar maximum length update kar do.

Ye approach tabhi sahi kaam karti hai jab array me negative numbers na hon,
kyunki negative aane par sum ka behavior fixed nahi rehta.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int longestSubarray(int[] nums, int k) {
        int left = 0;
        int right = 0;

        int maxlen = 0;
        int sum = 0;

        while(right < nums.length){
            while(left <= right && sum > k){
                sum -= nums[left];
                left++;
            }

            if(sum == k){
                maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, right - left + 1);
            }

            right++;
            if(right < nums.length){
                sum += nums[right];
            }
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
}
